24/04/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- A plane flying from Athens to Strasbourg, France made an emergency landing at Munich airport Monday morning (April 23rd) following a bomb threat. 
The Olympic Airlines flight had 137 people aboard, including 11 Greek members of the European Parliament. 
All passengers were safely evacuated shortly after landing and no bomb was found. 
Greece's NET TV reports that the threat was sent to an Athens police station but the flight number mentioned in it did not exist. 
Authorities reportedly decided to check the flight with the closest number. 
(AP, NET TV, Sky - 23/04/07)
